Geithner to Meet With Draghi, Monti, Sarkozy

-- B y   K e v i n   C o s t e l l o e
-- 
2011-12-02T17:43:22Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-02/geithner-to-meet-with-draghi-monti-sarkozy-during-europe-trip-next-week.html
U.S. Treasury Secretary  Timothy F.
Geithner  will visit Europe next week for meetings with officials
including European Central Bank President Mario Draghi, French
President Nicolas Sarkozy and Italian Prime Minister Mario
Monti, the Treasury said today.  The Treasury said in an e-mailed statement that Geithner
will hold “discussions with his counterparts on their efforts
to reinforce the institutions of the euro area” during his trip
from Dec. 6 to Dec. 8.  Geithner will also meet with Bundesbank President Jens
Weidmann and Spain’s Prime Minister-elect Mariano Rajoy, who,
according to the Treasury, “who will be in France for other
meetings.”  The trip will also take Geithner to Berlin for meeting with
German Finance Minister  Wolfgang Schaeuble  on Dec. 6, the
Treasury said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Kevin Costelloe at 
 kcostelloe@bloomberg.net  